## Code Node (stepType: `code`)

The Code node executes custom JavaScript in a sandboxed environment.

### Parameters
| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |
|-----------|------|---------|-------------|
| `language` | string | "javascript" | Only JavaScript supported currently |
| `codeContent` | string | - | The code to execute |
| `outputVariable` | string | - | Store result as variable |
| `timeoutSeconds` | number | 5 | Execution timeout (keep short!) |
| `maxRetries` | number | 0 | Retry count |

### Sandbox restrictions
- No require() -- no importing modules
- No fs -- no filesystem access
- No net/http -- no network calls (use HTTP node instead)
- No process -- no system access
- Timeout enforced (default 5s)

### What you CAN do
- JSON parsing and reshaping
- Math calculations
- String manipulation, regex
- Array operations (map, filter, reduce)
- Date formatting
- Data validation

### Available in sandbox
```javascript
// The variables object contains all workflow variables
const input = variables.input;
const prev = variables.lastOutput;
const ragData = variables.rag_results;

// Return value becomes the step output
return { processed: true, count: input.items.length };
```

### Runtime image: `hive/code-runner:latest`

### Example: Parse CSV to JSON
```javascript
const lines = variables.lastOutput.split('\n');
const headers = lines[0].split(',');
const rows = lines.slice(1).map(function(line) {
  const vals = line.split(',');
  const obj = {};
  headers.forEach(function(h, i) { obj[h.trim()] = (vals[i] || '').trim(); });
  return obj;
});
return rows;
```

### Example: Validate and reshape
```javascript
var data = JSON.parse(variables.lastOutput);
if (!data.email || data.email.indexOf('@') === -1) {
  return { valid: false, error: 'Invalid email' };
}
return { valid: true, user: { email: data.email, name: data.name || 'Unknown' } };
```
